The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

NATION BRIEFS

 Hyderabad, July 24 (PTI): A special CBI court today granted bail to Monica Bedi but her release from the city jail was delayed by a day.

 As the courts bail order could not reach the authorities at the womens jail in Chanchalguda before the 5.30pm deadline, the starlet will have to spend one more day in prison. 

 New Delhi (PTI): A teenaged domestic help from Bengal has alleged rape by a person running a placement agency and has also complained to police about her employer forcing her to have unnatural sex. The 14-year-old, who came to work at Kaveri Apartments in CR Park in south Delhi a year ago, has said she was raped by Gafur Mandal, 21, who runs the placement agency in Tughlaqabad, sources said. The complainant has also alleged that her employer, 58-year-old Purshottam Sahdev, who works in a public sector unit, forced her to have unnatural sex with him. No arrest has been made so far.

 New Delhi (PTI): The state consumer commission has asked Maruti Udyog Ltd to pay Rs 25,000 as compensation for allegedly selling a defective car in an auction to a person without giving an opportunity to inspect it. The commission also asked Maruti to refund the price of the car to the man.

 Jaipur (PTI): Five Bangladeshis have been arrested for conspiring to commit a crime and two sharp-edged weapons and a few iron rods have been seized from them, police said. They had been living illegally in the Pink City for the last six months. 

 New Delhi (PTI): Amaresh Bagchi, former director of the National Institute of Public Finance and Policy, has joined as a member of the newly constituted Commission on Centre-State Relations. 

 Nashik (PTI): As many as 55 school students from this city and districts will visit London between July 27 and August 8 to take part in a programme to mark the centenary of the scouts-guides movement.




